API's-----> Application programming interface.
It's a way to talk one s/w to another s/w.
It helps different app and system talk to each other and sharing data.

Client----> Customer(order some food) The one who make the request(Like a browser or an app)

API---> Waiter(Who talks with client and kitchen and who carry the data) The middle man that passes the request to the server and brings back the response.

Server---> Kitchen(where order gets prepared)---where all the processing happens(In the backend).


Type of API's
1. Haeware API's
Uploading a pht on Insta
camera uses Harware API to access ur camera
2. Software API's
Filter uses Software api to apply filter make our img appear better
3. Web api:   
 To upload the pht from ur phn to instagram's server.

Who Builts these API:
Dev create and use the API's
Dev follow below rukes while building web API's
REST
GRAPHQL
WEBSOCKETS
WEBHOOKS
SOAP


Which is most popolar:
Rest is stateless can save response(caching) and works with many data formats.

REST API:
It is a Tool, helps to create test and use API's easily
*
Collection: Is a folder-- whaere we store files

API request methods
GET--->READ
POST---> CREATE
PUT--->UPDATE
PATCH--->UPDATE
DELETE--->DELETE

API end point:
https://postman-echo.com/get
https://---->Protocol
postman-echo.com---> Host
get--->path

Status codes:
1. 1XX(100- 199)--->Informative(rearly usred)
2. 2XX(200- 299)---> Syccess
     201--->Created
     200---> Success
      204---> No content
3. 3XX(300- 399---> Redirection
      301---> Serource been moved permanently to another url
       302----> temporarly moved to diff url.
4. 4XX(400-499)----> client side error ex. tipo error
       401---> uncess
        403---?> forbidden
5. 5XX (500-599)---> Server side error
         502---> bad gateway



To add variable(No need to give complete url if we create a variable, just give path)
select the URL untill .com don't include path
Right click
select add variable
Give name and save




